<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-03-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-03-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="47" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Benavides</persName>,
                                    minister of foreign affairs, to Mr. <persName type="to">Perry</persName>, United States chargé d’affaires.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid,
                                            Palace</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-03-22"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 22,
                                        1865</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><seg type="margin">[473]</seg>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to reply to your
                                note of yesterday relative to the enlistment of seamen, which, it is
                                said, the confederate steamer Stonewall has effected at the Ferrol;
                                that the same day I transferred it to the minister of marine for him
                                to *adopt the proper measures to procure that the commander of said
                                vessel should set on shore the men which it seems he has
                                fraudulently embarked.</p>
                            <p>I avail myself of the occasion, &amp;c., &amp;c.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>A. BENAVIDES.</signed>
                            </closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p>The <hi rend="smallcaps">Chargé d’affaires</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">of the United States.</hi></p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>